commText: Saha and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Saha is on strike. Rabada will open the attack
Rabada to Saha, 1 run, back of a length around off, Saha inside halves the block behind the wicket and gets off the mark
Rabada to Shubman Gill, no run, good length ball on off, Gill defends with an open face towards point
Rabada to Shubman Gill, no run, I0$ short of length delivery, Gill turns it with soft hands to mid-wicket
Rabada to Shubman Gill, 1 run, I0$ on a length and nips in a tad, Gill inside halves the block to square leg and Saha crosses over

Rabada to Saha, FOUR, first time Rabada goes full and is driven to the boundary. Saha had the width outside off and he drives square on the off-side. There was a deep backward point in plact but he had no chance
Rabada to Saha, 1 run, I0$ fuller than good length, Saha opens the bat face and dabs it to deep backward point
Arshdeep Singh, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Saha, 1 run, I0$ leg-lined delivery and Saha flicks it to fine leg
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, no run, I0$ angled across the batter, Gill waits and steers it to point
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, good length ball around off, Gill plays it with soft hands in front of cover and quickly crosses over
Arshdeep Singh to Saha, 1 run, short of length delivery, Saha pulls along the ground to deep square leg
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, uses the angle going across and directs the ball to deep point
Arshdeep Singh to Saha, 1 run, fullish delivery at the stumps, Saha heaves it off the inner half to deep square leg
Rabada to Saha, no run, I0$ short of length delivery, Saha rides the bounce and punches to cover-point
Rabada to Saha, 1 run, back of a length around off, Saha steers it wide of short third and picks up an easy single
Rabada to Shubman Gill, no run, I0$ yorker on off-stump, Gill digs it off toe-end back to Rabada
Rabada to Shubman Gill, FOUR, that's classical Gill. Picks the short of length delivery and shovels it off the front foot over mid-wicket, just a short-arm jab and the ball flies away to the rope
Rabada to Shubman Gill, FOUR, back to back boundaries. Rabada overcorrects his length and feeds it on the pad, Gill flicks it through mid-wicket and there's no stopping that
Rabada to Shubman Gill, no run, on a length and outside off, Gill has a tentative poke and is beaten on the outside edge
Arshdeep Singh to Saha, 1 run, back of a length around off, Saha pats it to the vacant backward point pocket
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, swings back in sharply, Gill was planting his foot forward but adjusts quickly and knocks it to mid-off
Arshdeep Singh to Saha, 2 runs, fraction short in length, Saha pulls it behind square and picks up a brace
Arshdeep Singh to Saha, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Saha, out Caught by Ashutosh Sharma!! Saha looks at the toe of his bat. Arshdeep is not complaining. He's pumping his fists and celebrating. Punjab have an early wicket. Short of length delivery and seemed like Saha was through the pull early, caught it off the toe-end and the ball lobbbed to mid-wicket, simple catch for Ashutosh Sharma. Saha c Ashutosh Sharma b Arshdeep Singh 13(11) [4s-1]
Sai Sudharsan, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Arshdeep Singh to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, Sudharsan is off and running. Short and wide outside off, he cracks it behind point and the ball races away
Arshdeep Singh to Sai Sudharsan, no run, back of a length around off, Sudharsan steers it wide of slip and the fielder makes a diving stop
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, no run, good length ball around off, Gill prods forward and defends it back

Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, FOUR, cracking shot! I0$ fraction short delivery, Gill uses fast hands to cut the ball away square on the off-side. The deep backward point had no chance and didn't even try to chase

Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, now drops one with soft hands in front of mid-off and sets off, there's a direct hit but Gill was well in. Actually he plonked his bat in instead of sliding it and just made it before the stumps lit up
Harshal Patel to Sai Sudharsan, no run, slower ball around off, Sudharsan defends to the off-side
Harshal Patel to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, slower ball outside off, Sudharsan opens the bat face and directs square on the off-side
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, slower ball around off, Gill nudges it through the vacant mid-wicket region

Over Summary (1-5 ov) -- Saha collects a boundary vs Rabada -- Tidy over from Arshdeep -- Gill scores back-to-back fours off Rabada -- Saha falls to Arshdeep -- Sai Sudharsan gets going with a cracking cut shot
Sam Curran, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Sam Curran to Shubman Gill, 1 run, angled across off, Gill pushes it off the outer half to backward point
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, no run, I0$ fullish delivery and Sudharsan turns it to mid-on
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, no run, short of length close to off, Sudharsan tucks it to mid-wicket
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, full and at the stumps, Sudharsan flicks to deep square leg
Sam Curran to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, leg-lined delivery and Gill flicks it towards deep mid-wicket, races back for the second
Sam Curran to Shubman Gill, FOUR, that's a good way to end the powerplay. Short and angled across, Gill opens the bat face and cuts it square of the wicket
Harpreet Brar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, round the wicket, full ball with a slip in place, wristily driven to long-on
No slip for Gill
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 89.4kph, width on offer, cut away to deep point for a brace
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, non-turner on the stumps, knocked to long-off
Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 97.1kph, darted down leg and Sai Sudharsan gets low to sweep it to fine leg
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, no run, 91.5kph, bit of flight on this full ball, push-driven to the left of the bowler and Brar makes a diving stop
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 94.7kph, not short but the line allows Gill to crouch and cut it behind square on the off-side
Lowest run-rates in the Powerplay this season: 7.62 - GT 7.83 - PBKS 8.26 - RR 8.61 - CSK 8.61 - LSG
Spin from both ends now
Liam Livingstone, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 86.7kph, appeal for lbw, struck down. In-drifting offie from round the wicket, slides on with the arm and Sai Sudharsan is rapped on the pads as he gets forward to push. Big inside edge!
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, no run, goes back and hurriedly defends this middle-stump line ball
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, punched to sweeper cover off the back foot
Livingstone to Shubman Gill, FOUR, 90.9kph, legbreak but it's a half-tracker. Shubman Gill latches onto it. Short and wide, the captain cuts fiercely well in front of square
Livingstone to Shubman Gill, no run, 89.4kph, lands on middle and spins away, driven back to the bowler who mocks a throw at the batter

Livingstone to Shubman Gill, leg byes, 2 runs, 97.3kph, pitches outside leg, hardly any spin on this occasion and Gill tries to sweep it fine. No bat and the ball dribbles towards fine leg off the thigh pad
Strategic timeout! Risk-free cricket and GT get off to a solid start. Can Punjab's spinners inflict some damage?
Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 96.9kph, quick, flat and outside off, Sai Sudharsan stays back to cut hard and chops it towards backward point off the under-edge
Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 85kph, fuller ball, driven to long-off. Apparently Shubman Gill asked his batting partner to play with a straight bat after the previous ball
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, no run, 93.2kph, full delivery, push-driven to the left of the bowler who makes a diving stop. A big cheer from the crowd
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 99.6kph, fuller outside off, Gill eases the drive to sweeper cover

Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, 96.9kph, Punjab can't afford to bowl these freebies. Non-turner just down leg, Sai Sudharsan gets inside the line and gets low to sweep. Some wood on it and the ball dribbles away to fine leg for four
Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 95.1kph, the line is wider outside off and Sai Sudharsan scythes it to sweeper cover
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 91.4kph, full delivery on middle and leg, swept to fine leg
Livingstone to Shubman Gill, no run, 90.2kph, gets forward and drives with the spin to backward point
Livingstone to Shubman Gill, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Livingstone to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Rabada!! Livingstone is pumped up! The crowd find their voice. This is a big wicket! 92.9kph, fullish leggie from Livingstone and the GT captain decides to loft it downtown. The bat turns at the point of impact and the timing goes awry. More bat than distance. Rabada settles under the skier at long-off to take a safe catch. Shubman Gill c Rabada b Livingstone 35(29) [4s-5]
David Miller, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Livingstone to Miller, 1 run, fuller length ball, Miller gets off the mark by easing it to long-on
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, worked through backward square leg
Livingstone to Miller, no run, blocked back to the bowler. Very good over for Punjab!
Over Summary (6-10 ov) -- Gill ends the powerplay with a boundary -- The pair of Gill and Sai keep up with the asking rate -- Livingstone gets the big wicket of Gill
Kagiso Rabada [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Rabada to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 134.1kph, back of a length, tucked to deep square leg
Rabada to Miller, 1 run, 140.8kph, length ball, tapped with soft hands in front of point for a quick single
Rabada to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 137.8kph, short of length, Sai Sudharsan punches and Rossouw makes a sliding stop to his left at cover
A slight hold-up in play as Sai Sudharsan is receiving some treatment from the physio

Rabada to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 139.3kph, beaten! Rabada gets this short of a good length ball to nip away outside off, Sai Sudharsan punches sans any feet movement and the ball whistles past the outside edge
Rabada to Sai Sudharsan, no run, driven sweetly but Rossouw makes a diving stop to his right at cover
Rabada to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, finds the gap does the left-hander as he drives this fuller length ball to sweeper cover for a couple of runs
Livingstone to Miller, 1 run, 92.6kph, full on the stumps, driven down to long-on
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 93.3kph, full again, clipped towards midwicket and the batters decide against the second
Livingstone to Miller, wide, 84.9kph, Livingstone slides one down leg
Livingstone to Miller, 1 run, 92.9kph, flat and full, Miller skips down the track to drive along the ground to long-on
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 81.7kph, more flight, gets it to dip a bit and Sai Sudharsan drives to long-on
Livingstone to Miller, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Livingstone to Miller, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! The crowd erupts again. Bit of flight from Livingstone and that probably lured Miller into playing a big shot. The left-hander backs away to hoist it over wide long-on and misses it altogether. No turn and the ball crashes into the leg-stump. Game on! Miller b Livingstone 4(6)
Azmatullah Omarzai, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Livingstone to Azmatullah, 1 run, with a slip in place, Livingstone bowls a full ball and that's been driven down to long-off
Harpreet Brar [2.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Azmatullah, no run, 94.6kph, pushed back to the bowler off the inner part of the bat
Harpreet Brar to Azmatullah, 1 run, 89.4kph, length ball around off and Azmatullah cuts it to deep point
Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 91.3kph, cut straight to point
Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 94.3kph, leg-lined, clipped to the left of midwicket
Harpreet Brar to Azmatullah, SIX, this is what this guy can do! 95.2kph, touch too full from Brar, Omarzai clears his front leg, bends his back leg and pumps it over long-on

Harpreet Brar to Azmatullah, no run, good comeback from Brar. Pulls his length back by a fraction, cramps the batter for room in the process. Azmatullah backs away to force it through the off-side and gets an inside edge onto the pitch
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, no run, nudged to midwicket
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 92.3kph, full outside off, Sai Sudharsan eases the drive to long-off
Livingstone to Azmatullah, 1 run, 95.1kph, moves leg-side and gets low to slap it through extra cover. Doesn't get it anywhere close to the middle and the ball dribbles to long-off
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, bit of width on offer, Sai Sudharsan cuts to deep backward point
Livingstone to Azmatullah, 1 run, pushed through quicker by Livingstone, Omarzai stays leg-side and pushes towards cover for a quick single
Livingstone to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 92.6kph, full again, bunted to long-on. Livingstone finishes with impressive figures of 4-0-19-2!
Strategic timeout! Livingstone has brought back life into this contest by dismissing Gill and Miller. The asking rate is still under 9 RPO and GT have enough firepower
Sam Curran [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, full outside off, Sai Sudharsan drives and outside-edges to third man
Sam Curran to Azmatullah, 1 run, full outside off, Azmatullah drives hard to sweeper cover
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, 129.8kph, poor ball from Curran, strays a full ball onto the pads and Sai Sudharsan flicks it fine of the short fine leg fielder
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, out Bowled!! Chopped on! 128kph, length ball that doesn't bounce much outside off, Sai Sudharsan looks to ease it through the covers and ends up deflecting it onto the sticks via an inside edge. Curran punches the air in delight. Sai Sudharsan b Sam Curran 31(34) [4s-3]
Rahul Tewatia, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Sam Curran to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, leg-stump half-volley and Tewatia gets off the mark by glancing it fine of short fine leg. Easy!
Sam Curran to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 129.2kph, good length delivery, poked to point and the batters decide against the single
Harshal Patel [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack

Over Summary (11-15 ov) -- Rabada comes up and troubles Sai Sudharsan -- Livingstone cleans up Miller -- Omarzai breaks the shackles with a six off Brar -- Livingstone finishes with figures 4-0-19-2 -- Sudharsan chops one on, Curran with the wicket -- Tewatia gets off the mark with a four
Harshal Patel to Azmatullah, 2 runs, 123.8kph, low full toss, Azmatullah shapes to flick and gets a leading edge which takes the ball towards deep backward point
Harshal Patel to Azmatullah, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Azmatullah, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Edged and gone! 137.3kph, pacy full delivery from wide of the crease, Azmatullah stays leg-side and looks to drive/steer with an opened bat-face. Audible outside edge and it's a straightforward catch for the keeper. GT have now lost half their side. Azmatullah c Jitesh Sharma b Harshal Patel 13(10) [6s-1]
Shahrukh Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sai Sudharsan (31 off 34, SR: 91.17) is the second GT batter to strike at below run-a-ball in an IPL innings (minimum 25 balls faced) after Abhinav Manohar (26 off 33) against DC in Ahmedabad last year. \n \nSudharsan’s 31 off 34 is also the second slowest innings of 25 balls or more this season after Tanush Kotian’s 24 off 31 at the same venue last week.
Harshal Patel to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, 134.7kph, back of a length outside off, confidently punched to sweeper cover
Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, no run, full outside off from round the wicket, Tewatia gets forward and pushes it to backward point

Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 136.5kph, fuller than a length, Tewatia gets forward and defensively pushes it to the right of the bowler. Harshal half-stops it in his followthrough. Another dot!
Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, width on offer, slashed towards third man. Just 4 runs and a wicket off the over!
Harpreet Brar [3.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
Equation: 38 runs | 24 balls. Tewatia has won it from tougher positions against Punjab in the past

Harpreet Brar to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 103.9kph, premeditated reverse-sweep attempted by Tewatia and he misses the quick ball from Brar. Confident appeal, turned down and PBKS review. This looks close. UltraEdge confirms no bat/glove as the ball goes under the blade. Struck on the right thigh. Ball-tracking shows it to be pitching outside leg! PBKS lose a review
Harpreet Brar to Rahul Tewatia, 2 runs, 100.4kph, Rahul Tewatia allows the ball to come to him and nudges it towards midwicket for a couple
Harpreet Brar to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, not only does he connect, he also pierces the gap. Full outside off and Tewatia reverse-sweeps expertly between short third man and backward point
Harpreet Brar to Rahul Tewatia, 2 runs, 100.6kph, no fielder inside the circle on the on-side and Tewatia smartly takes a brace b turning this length ball gently towards the midwicket pocket
Harpreet Brar to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, 96.7kph, length ball around leg, Tewatia gets inside the line, gets low in the process and sweeps fiercely over short fine leg for a one-bounce four
Harpreet Brar to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, 97.3kph, width served, cut to deep backward point. 13 runs off the over and it's another wicketless outing for Brar
Equation: 25 runs | 18 balls. Here's Rabada to bowl his final over
Kagiso Rabada [3.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Rabada to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, shot! 136.6kph, length ball from round the wicket and Tewatia fiercely slap-drives through extra cover. Superb connection and the ball speeds away

Rabada to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, Rabada pulls his length back and slants it into the left-hander, cramping the batsman for room. Tewatia looks to dab it and the ball dies down on the leg-side off his glove. He's in a bit of pain
Rabada to Shahrukh Khan, SIX, 139.6kph, seam-up, fullish ball, Shahrukh Khan makes room and hits through the line. Gets under it and smokes it over long-off. Clean strike
Rabada to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, 141.6kph, Rabada slips in a yorker and Shahrukh brings his bat down hurriedly to jam it towards short fine leg

Rabada to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, audacious! Rahul Tewatia gives the charge to the bowler by dancing down the track, slightly moves leg-side in the process and smashes it over the bowler. No chance for mid-off to cut it off

Rabada to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, wow! 20 runs off the over. In-slanter, it looked like Tewatia was cramped for room but the left-hander has somehow managed to dab it just past the keeper. The ball runs away to third man for four more
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-11-1] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Shahrukh Khan, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Harshal Patel to Shahrukh Khan, out Bowled!! 125.4kph, yorker length, Shahrukh Khan looks to flick it away and he might have been early into his shot. The ball dipped on him and the batsman didn't pick the change of pace. The ball brushes Shahrukh's boot before hitting the base of the sticks. Shahrukh Khan b Harshal Patel 8(4) [6s-1]
Rashid Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshal Patel to Rashid Khan, 1 run, low full toss, clipped to midwicket
Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, no run, 125.1kph, full and outside off, Tewatia swings hard to go over mid-off but connects with thin air. Beaten on the outside edge
Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, driven to long-off
Harshal Patel to Rashid Khan, 2 runs, 138.6kph, low full toss, flicked away to deep backward square leg
Harshal Patel to Rashid Khan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Rashid Khan, out Caught by Rossouw!! 124.2kph, low full toss, Rashid Khan wristily flicks and Rossouw takes a superb low catch diving to his left at short midwicket. Rashid Khan c Rossouw b Harshal Patel 3(3)
Two wickets and just 4 runs off the 19th over. Should Harshal have bowled the 18th over? That's something Curran might be thinking now. Just one needed off the final over...
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-13-1] is back into the attack
Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Arshdeep Singh to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, 135.1kph, fullish ball strayed onto the pads and Rahul Tewatia flicks it away to fine leg for four. Gujarat Titans win by 3 wickets! Tewatia folds his hands and prays as he looks heavenwards...

23:08 Local Time, 17:38 GMT, 23:08 IST: All the five matches at this venue have gone to the final over, but the home team managed to win just one. Opting to bat, Punjab got off to a brisk start, thanks to Prabhsimran's blitz in the powerplay, but the troika of GT spinners ruled the roost in the middle overs as they finished with combined bowling figures of 7/68. Chasing 143, Gujarat lost Saha inside the powerplay once again. Sai Sudharsan joined his skipper and the equation was tailor-made for the duo. Shubman Gill was looking in good touch as well but his miscued loft resulted in GT stuttering a bit. Livingstone removed Gill and Miller to bring back life into this contest. Sai Sudharsan and Azmatullah were dismissed in quick succession and the Titans slipped from 77/1 to 103/4. With 38 runs needed off four overs, the game was pretty much in the balance. That's when I0$ He struck a couple of boundaries against Brar and Rabada conceded 20 runs off the 18th over which extinguished Punjab's hopes. Harshal picked a couple of wickets in the penultimate over but that only delayed the proceedings.

Sam Curran | PBKS captain: I think so (we were 10-15 short). The effort with the ball was incredible, the commitment and fight was amazing, but it was not enough. The Afghanistan spinners are world class bowlers and Sai Kishore bowled really well, credit to them. That is the third time we have used that pitch, anything above 160 would have been a par total but we still fought well. Prabhsimran played really well in the powerplay but unfortunately we lost a cluster of wickets after that. Now we know what to do, we have to win every game.
GT in run-chases: Matches: 23 Wins: 17 Defeats: 6 Win%: 73.91 Each of the five matches between PBKS and GT have been won by the chasing side.
Tewatia in run-chases vs PBKS since 2020: Inns: 5 Runs: 109 Avg: 54.5 SR: 187.93 4s/6s: 8/9
Tewatia in successful run-chases for GT Inns: 10 Runs: 224 Avg: 112 SR: 163.50 HS: 43* 4s/6s: 26/9

Shubman Gill | GT captain: Would have liked to finish it a bit early, but good to get those two points. (Captaincy) It's been very exciting for me to be able to take up this role. Except for the over-rate, everything has been good. When I am out there batting, I just want to play as a batter, I don't want to think too much about the captaincy. He (Livingstone) was trying to rush me there but the ball that I got out, I would have made that decision even if I was batting as a batsman or even without that little bit that we had (small altercation).

Sai Kishore | Player of the Match: Just trying to give my 120% for the team, playing after 20-25 days, so just wanted to go there, enjoy myself and give my everything. Ashish Nehra has created a beautiful environment where we can be fearless and play for the team no matter what the result is. He told me to enjoy myself and gave me a lot of freedom to express myself. Instinctively I felt into the wicket and just change of pace was the way to go here, it worked out beautifully. Credit to everyone who showed up today. Rahul played an amazing knock once again. Rashid and Noor bowled beautifully, overall complete team effort.

A high-scoring thriller at the Eden Gardens followed by a last-over finish here in Mullanpur which hosted its final match of the season. PBKS and RCB remain at the bottom of the table with just 4 and 2 points respectively after playing eight matches each. Not a convincing win for the Titans but with these two crucial points, they climb up to the sixth spot. That's it for today. Tune in tomorrow for I0$. For now, it's goodbye and good night.
